"""
QUESTION 1.1 (py_01_exe.py - Personal Information Calculator)
================================================================================
Create a program that:
1. Takes user input for: full name, age, height (meters), and weight (kg)
2. Calculates:
   - Birth year (assume current year is 2025)
   - BMI (Body Mass Index) = weight / (height²)
3. Displays a summary with all information
4. Classifies BMI into categories:
   - BMI < 18.5: Underweight
   - 18.5 ≤ BMI < 24.9: Normal weight
   - 25 ≤ BMI < 29.9: Overweight
   - BMI ≥ 30: Obese

Expected Output (example):
    Personal Information Summary:
    Name: John Doe
    Age: 30
    Birth Year: 1995
    BMI: 24.50
    BMI Category: Normal weight
"""

